While developing SmartSpend we took into consideration basic programming ethics. 
Our program was written using our own original code. However we used resources 
such as W3Schools to learn basic programming skills, and also our teacher helped 
us in understanding basic programming and different code functions.

These resources helped us understand concepts such as loops, condition statements,
and error handling, which were important in making the program work properly. While
these resources helped us learn how certain parts of Python work, the actual
program and structure of SmartSpend were still written by us. We made sure that the
logic, organization, and design of the program were our own work.

